title: For Sale:  Hand Made 1:3 Scale Miniature Colt M1911 Gun Firearms w/ Walnut Presentation Box
postcontent:
For sale is a rare jewel of an object. A hand made miniature 1:3 scale Colt M1911 complete with walnut presentation box and 7 rounds of brass ammunition (dummies). Every piece of this pistol is hand milled from solid brass and then cast in pure .925 silver with hand made rose wood grips. This masterpiece took almost 2 months to be completed. 

For generations this small consortium of gifted craftsmen have been painstakingly milling and assembling a variety of historically relevant miniature firearms from scratch on a commissioned basis. These 1:3 miniature Colt 1911's aren't just accurate from the outside but are actually composed from over 60 working parts just like the actual automatic pistol. In fact they are required to plug the center of each barrel in accordance with very strict gun control laws present in certain countries due to their functional realism. Each component is completely assembled by hand. There is accuracy down to the jewelry laser inscribed etchings and serial number on the gun.

This miniature Colt functions just like its real big brother. The clip can be removed and loaded with the hand made brass .45 caliber bullets. The slide can by cycled back loading and ejecting a round. The slide lock holds the slide back when an empty magazine is inserted and releases the slide when dropped. The hammer lock keeps the Colt in "cocked and locked" position identical to that of the real automatic. The trigger can be depressed dropping the hammer. It's a perfect replica of the Colt only one third the size.

These miniature firearms are truly AMAZING feats of manufacturing that must be seen to be believed. Included with this beautiful matte silver finished Colt M1911 is a hand made, felt lined walnut presentation box which holds the pistol along with its 7 miniature rounds of .45 caliber brass ammunition.

Melonite Nitriding treatment turns a standard chrome moly steel barrel into a very slick, hard and corrosion resistant barrel. Unlike chrome lining, the Melonite process is a treatment done to the surface instead of adding a layer of material. This treatment is done to both the inside and outside of the barrel. The slick surface will never peel, is thicker than chrome lining, will not negatively affect accuracy as chrome lining does and will reduce the amount of friction created. Less friction equals less bore surface wear which will extend the barrel life. Another added benefit is carbon does not easily adhere to this surface making your cleaning job that much easier.  This technology has been used by Glock, Springfield and Heckler & Koch for years and is gaining popularity as more companies are offering their products with this treatment.

title: For Sale:  Hand Made 1:6 Scale Miniature Smith & Wesson M36 Chiefs Special
postcontent:
A truly precious silver jewel of an object, for sale is a completely hand made and assembled miniature 1:6 scale Smith & Wesson M36 Chief's Special complete with 5 rounds of miniature brass ammunition (dummies). Milled from solid brass, every piece of the pistol is then cast in pure .925 silver and hand assembled. The finish is then blued and miniature wooden grips are screwed in. This beauty took over a month to complete. 

For generations this small consortium of gifted craftsmen have been painstakingly milling and assembling a variety of historically relevant miniature firearms from scratch on a commissioned basis. This 1:6 miniature S&W M36 Chief's Special is not only accurately recreated in scale from the outside but is actually composed from 20 separate working parts just like the actual revolver. Each component is completely assembled by hand. Every detail down to the jewelry laser inscribed etchings is accurate.

This miniature S&W functions like its real big brother. The spinning cylinder (must be spun by hand, does not index automatically) which can be opened and closed by means of a tiny release, can be loaded with 5 rounds of the handmade brass .38 caliber ammunition. The hammer can be pulled to the rear position and cocked. Pulling the trigger releases the hammer (of course the pistol DOES NOT actually fire). It's a perfect replica of the Smith & Wesson M36 only one sixth its original size.

These miniature firearms are truly AMAZING feats of manufacturing that must be seen to be believed. Included with this beautiful .925 silver with blued finish S&W Chief's Special are 5 miniature handmade .38 caliber bullets and a white leather glass top presentation box.


- THIS 1:6 SCALE FIREARM WILL NOT FIRE LIVE AMMUNITION OF ANY SORT.  IT IS SOLELY TO BE APPRECIATED AS A MINIATURE WORK OF ART -


Please contact me for additional information or photographs. Special orders can also be placed for the same gun with ivory grips. Numerous other miniature firearms (eg. 1:6 or 1:3 scale Colt 1911) are also available upon request. 

*Care instructions will be provided following purchase.
